==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ichthyol
<hw>Ich"thy*ol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'ichqy`s</grk>, <grk>-y`os</grk>, a fish + (prob.) L.
<ets>ol</ets>eum oil; but cf. <er>Ichthyolite</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An oily substance prepared by the dry
distillation of a bituminous mineral containing fossil fishes. It is
used in medicine as a remedy in some forms of skin diseases.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

